File: lichen/subsys/lichen/routing/include/lichen/routing/announce.h
Line: 69

The header declares:
    int lichen_announce_ingest_authenticated(
        const uint8_t *_Nonnull data, size_t len,
        const struct lichen_announce_rx_meta *_Nonnull meta);

But the implementation in announce.c lines 252-257 explicitly handles NULL meta:

    if (meta == NULL) {
        default_meta.observed_uptime_s = k_uptime_get_32() / 1000U;
        meta = &default_meta;
    }

The _Nonnull annotation tells callers and static analyzers that NULL is not allowed, but the implementation accepts and handles NULL. This is:
1. API contract violation (header lies about requirements)
2. May cause caller warnings/errors for passing NULL when it's actually valid
3. Static analysis tools will not catch missing NULL checks in callers

Either remove _Nonnull from the header, or remove the NULL handling from the implementation and require callers to always provide metadata.
